cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.NI, cs.DC

The paper proposes a method for adaptive streaming of 360-degree videos, which involves techniques related to multimedia (cs.MM), computer vision (cs.CV), and graphics (cs.GR). The method also considers network issues, such as bitrate adaptation and prioritization, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
